  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\nRight now validate gossip messages separately (but do them concurrently), we could try to verify them in batch\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\n- Refactor gossip queue with keeping `add()` as is (add 1 item) but `next()` takes multiple items from the queue\r\n- all `validateGossip*` functions should take an array of messages instead of 1 message\r\n  - Phase 0: do all verifications except for signature verification\r\n  - Phase 1: do signature verification for all *valid* messages after phase 0\r\n    - Aggregate pubkeys/signatures before doing signature verification\r\n    - If one of them fails, retry with doing them separately (like the current flow)\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\n\r\n- Consider if it's worth to index the attestation queue by target root, in order to regen state leveraging the work of @dapplion \r\n- Alternative would be to use the current SeenAttestationDatas cache, just improve the signature verification, state regen may not be the bottle neck for now\r\n",
